article.headline: Sacred Heart 70, Wagner 62
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Drew Shubik scored 17 points to lead four Sacred Heart players in double figures and the Pioneers beat Wagner 70-62 on Saturday night. Jarrid Frye, Brice Brooks and Kibwe Trim each added 10 points for Sacred Heart (7-8, 4-2 Northeast Conference), which beat the Seahawks 61-50 last Saturday. Durell Vinson was 9-for-14 from the field and had 19 points for the Seahawks (8-5, 1-3), while DeEarnest McLemore added 12. Shubik had five points in a 7-0 run to open the second half that put Pioneers up 41-35 with 17:13 to play. Ryon Howard's jumper gave Sacred Heart a 46-37 lead with 14:25 left, but Wagner got within 56-55 on Jason Rudakas' three-point play with 4:54 to go. Frye his two 3-pointers in a 14-4 run that gave the Pioneers their biggest lead, 70-59 with 26 seconds remaining.
